                    },
                    "page": 38,
                    "errata": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "2.0",
                        "alt": "2.0",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 32
                    }
                }
            ],
            "html": "The behir is a massive, serpentine beast with never fewer than a dozen short legs, each ending in three hooked talons. A behir can live to 80 years, but most perish far younger to violence. Fully grown, a behir is 40 feet long and weighs 4,000 pounds.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Beast</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"2\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Arcana</a></u>, <u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 24"
        },
        {
            "name": "Hatred of Dragons",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 38",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 38",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                    },
                    "page": 38,
                    "errata": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "2.0",
                        "alt": "2.0",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 32
                    }
                }
            ],
            "subtype": "sidebar",
            "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
            "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
            "image": {
                "type": "image",
                "name": "Additional Lore",
                "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
            },
            "html": "Some scholars have speculated that behirs are somehow related to <a aonid=\"34\" game-obj=\"MonsterFamilies\">blue dragons</a>, citing their reptilian features, lightning breath, and ability to speak the <a aonid=\"2\" game-obj=\"Languages\">Draconic</a> language, but such scholars would do well to keep such opinions from behirs they encounter in the field. Nothing infuriates a behir faster than likening it to a dragon!"
        }
    ],
